---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Governance"
  description="Operating principles for how this site and its projects stay legible over time."
>
  <section class="section">
    <p class="section-kicker">Governance</p>
    <h1 class="section-title">Governance is an operating practice here, not a compliance badge.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      The role of governance on this site is to keep language, evidence, and review habits aligned
      as the body of work grows.
    </p>
  </section>

  <ol class="governance-list">
    <li>Prefer static artifacts over systems that need authentication, databases, or hosted backends.</li>
    <li>Make claims in proportion to the evidence that can be shown on the page.</li>
    <li>Keep information architecture stable enough that essays and projects can reference each other.</li>
    <li>Use projects as proof points for ideas instead of treating the project list as a vanity portfolio.</li>
    <li>Keep documentation minimal so the public surface area stays readable and maintainable.</li>
  </ol>
</BaseLayout>
